<subSubSection id="8BD17236DEEAF6C7905EC2A79F2D9B73" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4AC998B8691627D3BF1DED03BF8C151E" pageNumber="236">
Le type de 
<taxonomicName id="062F97A2A796D58122B57BB17DDEE18F" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:147791" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Formica" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Formica megacephala Leach" lsidName-HNS="Formica megacephala Leach" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megacephala">Formica megacephala</taxonomicName>
provenait de l'ile de France et appartenait a la collection Bosc, conservee au Museum de Paris. M. L. Berlaud a eu l'obligeance, sur ma requete, de rechercher ce type au Museum; mais cet insecte ne s'est pas trouve.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6FAA24059459EEC1D23A36E1C1018E4C" lastPageNumber="237" pageNumber="236">
On doit a Roger l'attribution du nom fabricien a l'espece qui jusqu'alors etait designee sous le nom de 
<taxonomicName id="49EA4F68BE52C53C593DEFA5E36C5560" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:138310" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Formica" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Formica pusilla De Geer" lsidName-HNS="Formica pusilla De Geer" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusilla">pusilla Heer</taxonomicName>
. Cet auteur avait recu de l'ile Maurice des 
<taxonomicName id="F27FF164BF1415C5AD8AB73C8E2308DB" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:24885" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole Westwood" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole Westwood" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pheidole</taxonomicName>
qui concordaient fort bien avec la description ancienne et qui d'ailleurs etaient identiques (du moins selon l'opinion de Roger) a 
<taxonomicName id="0CA062795B0AD57B7FB57DC8D161E76B" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:188668" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole pusilla (Heer)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole pusilla (Heer)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusilla">Ph. pusilla</taxonomicName>
de Madere. Au Musee de Berlin, qui renferme une partie de la collection de Roger, ces exemplaires n'existent pas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A6C1DFDD75D6C31A0CF9046FFFD507A8" pageNumber="237">
Il ne m'a pas ete possible de me procurer des topotypes de l'ile en question: les grands musees de Paris, de Londres et de Berlin n'en possedent pas. Il est vraisemblable que le type de la collection Bosc se rapportait a la serie spinosa-scabrior, qui abonde a Madagascar, a la Reunion et aux Sechelles, et qui est extremement voisin de 
<taxonomicName id="3801BD3C07B931816F76E7FD197A6F14" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:188668" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole pusilla (Heer)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole pusilla (Heer)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusilla">pusilla</taxonomicName>
; mais je ne saurais l'affirmer avec certitude.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="126DC971810CC06EA9B6C8F0D2FA29CD" pageNumber="237">
En consequence de ce qui vient d'etre dit, je maintiens le nom de 
<taxonomicName id="27108B2948D8F868EA8ED5FA86AFF7FC" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33860" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole megacephala (Fabricius)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole megacephala (Fabricius)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megacephala">Ph. megacephala (F.)</taxonomicName>
comme nom d'espece, sans designer formellement aucun type. Mais on pourra regarder la forme la plus anciennement decrite (
<taxonomicName id="38E23A864376FEE9C6513DFC9C2F65E9" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:188668" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole pusilla (Heer)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole pusilla (Heer)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusilla">Ph. pusilla Heer</taxonomicName>
) comme type, et lui rapporter, comme sous-especes et varietes, les formes publiees successivement (1).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DB7E9CAF8E4FD7AB62554E70337463D2" pageNumber="237">
M. Forel ecrivait en 1905: Â« L'augmentation de nos connaissances sur les 
<taxonomicName id="DAB92652DDA5E83ACFD14344208DB26C" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:24885" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole Westwood" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole Westwood" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pheidole</taxonomicName>
m'amene a separer specifiquement la 
<taxonomicName id="E8030A222975B2AE13080D3584F0B91B" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33949" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole punctulata Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole punctulata Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctulata">Ph. punctulata Mayr</taxonomicName>
de la 
<taxonomicName id="AAA118429672FCA093D1939193589AE0" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33860" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole megacephala (Fabricius)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole megacephala (Fabricius)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megacephala">megacephala</taxonomicName>
. Les sexes ailes de la race 
<taxonomicName id="8FB993A4C808D74DF46736734B379EF9" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33927" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole picata Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole picata Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picata">picata</taxonomicName>
en particulier ont les ailes beaucoup plus longues et les nervures plus pales que la 
<taxonomicName id="F7356265087D3DF48B9A967338C04234" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33860" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole megacephala (Fabricius)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole megacephala (Fabricius)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megacephala">megacephala</taxonomicName>
. Je rattache donc les formes malgaches comme sous-especes a la 
<taxonomicName id="9A763E0FF4253F61FF4AE6CA868485F9" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33949" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole punctulata Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole punctulata Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctulata">punctulata</taxonomicName>
Â» (Ann. Soc Ent. Belg., vol. 49, p. 163).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="49DCC8DA94A2E7B2BC3B4EE9ED9C5206" pageNumber="237">
Ceci est exact, quant a 
<taxonomicName id="5E25ACDD19455F4D483C20825173FDDD" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33927" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole picata Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole picata Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picata">Ph. picata</taxonomicName>
, qui merite d'etre separee comme espece, non seulement de 
<taxonomicName id="7A9C2A349975F406ABA4E70A141D56EB" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33860" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole megacephala (Fabricius)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole megacephala (Fabricius)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megacephala">megacephala</taxonomicName>
, mais aussi de 
<taxonomicName id="7D20B9168E3601856F1A95AD703EB861" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33949" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole punctulata Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole punctulata Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctulata">punctulata</taxonomicName>
. Mes etudes sur la tete des [[ soldier ]] et des [[ worker ]] me portent a cela. Les sexes ailes de la serie malgache, spinosa-scabrior, n'ont pas les ailes remarquablement plus longues que 
<taxonomicName id="B8FAA4E7EFBBEDD2EAC058B2658F09BC" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:188668" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole pusilla (Heer)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole pusilla (Heer)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusilla">pusilla</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D98BC5352414AF1EE3A6CF5904F1B90A" pageNumber="237">A premiere vue il semble qu'on pourrait tres facilement separer</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
